patlak@med.uvm.edu (Joe Patlak) writes:

> Would it not be equally acceptable to put your public key in a .plan
> file so that it would be listed by the finger program.  If you need a
> public key from an individual who's machine you know, finger 
> individual@machine would deliver it to you.

Nah, doesn't work... :-( Several sites (including ours) have disabled
the possibility to be fingered from the net, for security reasons...

Another idea is to design a new protocol, similar to that of finger,
but simpler, which does only one thing - returns the public key of a
particular user. Any volunteers to write the appropriate RFC?

Regards,
Vesselin

